6. System Architecture
Frontend

The frontend is developed using Streamlit, providing a simple and interactive interface where users enter their learning challenges and receive AI-generated emotional analysis.

Backend

The backend is developed in Python, integrating deep learning models, rule-based keyword enhancement, and Google Gemini AI for personalized guidance.

AI Engine

The system processes user input through:

Text Preprocessing
Emotion Classification
Mixed Emotion Detection
Confidence Score Calculation
AI Response Generation
Database

The application stores interaction history and prediction results in CSV files for analytics and future improvements.

7. User Workflow
User enters learning problem
        │
        ▼
Text Preprocessing
        │
        ▼
Emotion Detection
(BERT + BiLSTM)
        │
        ▼
Mixed Emotion Analysis
        │
        ▼
Gemini AI Response Generation
        │
        ▼
Display Personalized Guidance
        │
        ▼
Save Results to CSV
        │
        ▼
Analytics Dashboard
8. Target Users
Scenario 1 – Educators & Academic Support Teams

Teachers and teaching assistants can analyze student concerns quickly. The platform automatically detects emotions and suggests appropriate responses, reducing manual effort and improving consistency.

Scenario 2 – Students & Self-Learners

Students can describe their academic challenges in natural language and instantly receive emotion-aware guidance, helping them overcome learning difficulties more efficiently.

